{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Related-Sessions","text":"Related Sessions","type":"heading"},{"items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-225-Advances-in-Camera-Capture-and-Photo-Segmentation","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-503-Creating-Photo-and-Video-Effects-Using-Depth"],"style":"list","type":"links"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19"]]},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC19","role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"Introducing Photo Segmentation Mattes"},"kind":"article","sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2019\/260","overridingTitle":"Watch Video (15 min)","isActive":true}},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-260-Introducing-Photo-Segmentation-Mattes","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-260-introducing-photo-segmentation-mattes"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Photos captured in Portrait Mode on iOS 12 contain an embedded person segmentation matte that made it easy to create creative visual effects like background replacement. iOS 13 leverages on-device machine learning to provide new segmentation mattes for any captured photo. Learn about the new semantic segmentation mattes available to you from both AVCapture and Core Image to isolate a person’s hair, skin, and teeth. Using any of these individual mattes or combining all of them, your app can now offer a tremendous amount of photo editing control.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"references":{"WWDC19.jpeg":{"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC19.jpeg","type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19.jpeg"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","abstract":[{"text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-225-Advances-in-Camera-Capture-and-Photo-Segmentation":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-225-Advances-in-Camera-Capture-and-Photo-Segmentation","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-225-advances-in-camera-capture-and-photo-segmentation","abstract":[{"text":"Powerful new features in the AVCapture API let you capture photos and video from multiple cameras simultaneously. Photos now benefit from semantic segmentation that allows you to isolate hair, skin, and teeth in a photo. Learn how these advances enable you to create great camera apps and easily achieve stunning photo effects.","type":"text"}],"title":"Advances in Camera Capture & Photo Segmentation","type":"topic"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-503-Creating-Photo-and-Video-Effects-Using-Depth":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-503-Creating-Photo-and-Video-Effects-Using-Depth","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-503-creating-photo-and-video-effects-using-depth","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The TrueDepth camera in the iPhone X streams high-quality depth data in real time allowing you to enhance your photo and video apps in fun and creative ways. Dive deep into the principles and best practices for working with depth data, learn how to use the new Portrait Segmentation API for still images, and see how these techniques can create special effects like background replacement and perspective changes."}],"title":"Creating Photo and Video Effects Using Depth","type":"topic"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"title":"Learn More…","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Learn More…","type":"text"}],"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2019/260":{"checksum":null,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2019\/260","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2019\/260","type":"download"},"WWDC19-Icon.png":{"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC19-Icon.png","type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-Icon.png"}]},"WWDCNotes.png":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"image","alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 11, Swift 5.1, iOS 13, macOS 10.15 (Catalina), tvOS 13, watchOS 6."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Combine"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Core Haptics"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Create ML"},{"type":"text","text":", and more."}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19","kind":"article","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC19-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC19.jpeg"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WW